bib_record.title: Scattering of 1-GeV protons on Si-28, S-32 and S-34.

free_txt: in Russian
in English
Experimental data on elastic and
inelastic scattering of 1-GeV protons from nuclei.
Tables 12-14.
.The diffractional multiple scattering theory.
Only statistical errors are given in data
table.
The total error in determining the absolute
values of the differential cross sections is
estimated to be -10%.
Chemical purity targets, 2*5*5-mm sizes, were used.
All data was taken from LIJAF preprint.
The differential cross sections for scattering on 28Si
and 32S were normalized in the region of the second
diffraction maximum (Angle = 8.5 degr.) by comparing
the areas under the elastic scattering peaks for these
nuclei and for hydrogen. In these measurements mixed
targets containing an admixture of polyethylene (CH2)
were used.
